race.comment: Wiggins sticks aboard PEPPERDINE (1) and the Pierro gelding is the one to beat building on his 4.6L win at Mackay over this trip. He has the early speed to manage the awkward gate and is a 2x winner third-up. ONE THING COUNTS (3) presents fitter for the sharp Clinton Taylor yard and was only beaten 1L here last time in stronger grade. He's won third-up and Butler will give him every chance from an inside barrier. PEAKING TOM (8) draws the inside barrier and gets back in his races. With average luck he's going well enough to get into the finish. PREPOTENT (2) won a 70 here two back and wasn't far away last time over shorter. Maps for a soft run on the quick back-up and is well in the mix.
